-- 3.1 PIPELINE RUN AUDIT
-- Table: ecomsphere.governance.pipeline_run_audit
-- ============================================================
--
-- PURPOSE
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- Stores execution-level audit records for pipeline runs.
--
-- This table answers questions such as:
--   - Did the pipeline run?
--   - Which task failed?
--   - When did the task start and end?
--   - How many records were processed?
--   - What error occurred?
--
-- TYPICAL COLUMNS
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
--   run_id
--   pipeline_name
--   layer_name
--   task_name
--   status
--   started_ts
--   ended_ts
--   records_processed
--   error_message
--   created_ts
--
-- GRAIN
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- One row per pipeline task execution event.
--
-- Example:
-- A single run_id may produce multiple rows:
--   - source_readiness_check
--   - rdbms_to_bronze
--   - adls_to_bronze
--   - bronze_to_silver
--   - silver_dq_metrics
--   - silver_to_gold
--   - gold_reconciliation
--
-- HOW IT GETS POPULATED
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- Most realistically in this project:
--   - Airflow generates the pipeline run context
--   - Airflow passes run_id / execution context to Databricks jobs
--   - Databricks notebooks or job wrappers log task execution rows
--   - optionally Airflow success/failure callbacks also write audit rows
--
-- SIMPLE ANSWER
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- Yes, in a realistic implementation this table should be
-- populated through Airflow orchestration logic directly or
-- indirectly.
--
-- RECOMMENDED DESIGN
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- Best practice:
--   - Airflow controls the run
--   - Databricks tasks perform processing
--   - Databricks task/notebook writes task-level metrics
--   - Airflow may also write orchestration-level status
--
-- ============================================================



