-- 3.4 SCHEMA REGISTRY
-- Table: ecomsphere.governance.schema_registry
-- ============================================================
--
-- PURPOSE
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- Stores schema versions and approval status for governed datasets,
-- especially Auto Loader file feeds.
--
-- This table answers questions such as:
--   - What schema versions existed for this dataset?
--   - Which version is approved?
--   - Was a new column detected?
--   - Was a datatype change rejected?
--
-- TYPICAL COLUMNS
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
--   dataset_name
--   version_no
--   schema_json
--   effective_ts
--   approval_status
--   approved_by
--   change_note
--
-- GRAIN
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- One row per dataset schema version.
--
-- HOW IT GETS POPULATED
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- Most realistic flow in this project:
--   - Auto Loader detects a schema change
--   - a Databricks schema-monitoring notebook compares current schema
--     with the registered approved schema
--   - if a change is found, a new schema version row is inserted
--   - approval_status may start as PENDING
--   - governance/data engineer later updates it to APPROVED or REJECTED
--
-- WHO POPULATES IT
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- Usually:
--   - Databricks schema monitoring job/notebook
--   - possibly triggered through Airflow
--   - approval update may be manual or workflow-driven
--
-- SIMPLE UNDERSTANDING
-- ------------------------------------------------------------
-- This is the change control register for schema evolution.
--
-- ============================================================



